---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";

const updated = "2026-04-30";
---

<Layout title="Now — Tim Raysby">
  <p class="text-xs font-mono uppercase tracking-widest text-green mb-4 flex items-center gap-3">
    <span class="w-8 h-px bg-green"></span>
    Now
  </p>
  <h1 class="font-serif text-4xl md:text-5xl font-light tracking-tight">
    Currently shipping.
  </h1>
  <p class="mt-2 text-xs font-mono text-ink-dimmer">Updated {updated}.</p>

  <div class="mt-12 space-y-10">
    <article>
      <p class="font-mono text-xs text-green-deep">[01]</p>
      <h2 class="font-serif text-2xl mt-2">Building NEXUS</h2>
      <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-ink-dim font-mono max-w-prose">Local-first personal AI infrastructure. Voice control, autonomous research, content production — all on a single workstation, no cloud dependency.</p>
    </article>

    <article>
      <p class="font-mono text-xs text-green-deep">[02]</p>
      <h2 class="font-serif text-2xl mt-2">Shipping this site</h2>
      <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-ink-dim font-mono max-w-prose">Astro on Cloudflare Workers. The page you are reading is the first proof.</p>
    </article>

    <article>
      <p class="font-mono text-xs text-green-deep">[03]</p>
      <h2 class="font-serif text-2xl mt-2">Writing weekly</h2>
      <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-ink-dim font-mono max-w-prose">Sunday newsletter on local-first AI for operators who do not want to pay rent on intelligence.</p>
    </article>
  </div>

  <section class="mt-20 pt-12 border-t border-charcoal-lighter">
    <h2 class="text-xs font-mono uppercase tracking-widest text-green mb-8 flex items-center gap-3">
      <span class="w-8 h-px bg-green"></span>
      NEXUS inspirations
    </h2>
    <p class="text-sm text-ink-dim font-mono max-w-prose mb-8">Operators whose work shapes how I think about local-first AI.</p>
    <ul class="space-y-4 text-sm text-ink-dim font-mono max-w-prose">
      <li class="flex gap-4"><span class="text-green-deep shrink-0">[01]</span><span><span class="text-ink">IndyDevDan</span> &mdash; autonomous coding workflows that ship real software.</span></li>
      <li class="flex gap-4"><span class="text-green-deep shrink-0">[02]</span><span><span class="text-ink">AllAboutAI</span> &mdash; local LLM stacks and the case against renting intelligence.</span></li>
      <li class="flex gap-4"><span class="text-green-deep shrink-0">[03]</span><span><span class="text-ink">NetworkChuck</span> &mdash; homelab as the operator's natural platform.</span></li>
      <li class="flex gap-4"><span class="text-green-deep shrink-0">[04]</span><span><span class="text-ink">Matthew Berman</span> &mdash; agentic systems built in the open.</span></li>
      <li class="flex gap-4"><span class="text-green-deep shrink-0">[05]</span><span><span class="text-ink">Nate B Jones</span> &mdash; AI strategy without the hype cycle.</span></li>
      <li class="flex gap-4"><span class="text-green-deep shrink-0">[06]</span><span><span class="text-ink">David Ondrej</span> &mdash; agentic AI for builders, not consumers.</span></li>
    </ul>
  </section>
</Layout>
